Improving UPI Payment Failure Experience
🧩 Problem :
UPI payment failures create frustration due to:
Lack of clear error messages
No guidance on next steps
Trust issues with digital payments
💡 Solution :
Redesigned the payment failure experience to:
Provide clear failure reasons
Suggest actionable next steps
Improve user trust and completion rates
🎯 My Role :
Analyzed user pain points
Designed improved user flow
Proposed product changes
⚙️ Key Improvements :
Clear error categorization (bank issue, network, insufficient funds)
Retry suggestions based on failure type
Status tracking for pending payments
📊 Impact : 
Reduced user confusion during failed transactions
Increased likelihood of retrying payments
Improved trust in digital payment systems
🧠 Product Thinking :
Insight
“Users don’t mind failure—they mind not knowing what to do next.”
🚀 Future Scope
Smart retry automation
Predictive failure detection
Integration with customer support
